question: Anna has 11 jars of icing in her storage room. Each jar of icing can decorate 15 cookies. Anna wants to bake enough cookies to use up all of her icing. If each pan holds 11 cookies, how many pans worth of cookies should she bake?
answer:
She has enough icing for 11 * 15 = <<11*15=165>>165 cookies.
She needs 165 / 11 = <<165/11=15>>15 pans to bake all of the cookies.
#### 15
